You can embed live preview examples into documentation pages (like this one!) as well as on pages outside of Lookbook.

## Embedding previews in pages within Lookbook

Preview embeds can be added to pages using the `embed` helper and any point in your document.

An embedded component preview looks like this: 

<%= embed Feedback::BlankSlateComponentPreview, :default, params: { icon: true } %>

To specify which preview example to render, the helper accepts a **preview class** and a **method name** (as a symbol) as it's arguments:

```erb
&lt;%= embed Feedback::BlankSlateComponentPreview, :default %&gt;
```

**Preview params** can be supplied if required:

```erb
&lt;%= embed Feedback::BlankSlateComponentPreview, :default,
  params: { icon: true } %&gt;
```

### Displaying inspector panels

You can specify a list of panels to display in the embed, underneath the preview itself:

```erb
&lt;%= embed Feedback::BlankSlateComponentPreview, :default,
  panels: [:source, :params] %&gt;
```

<%= embed Feedback::BlankSlateComponentPreview, :default, panels: %w[source params] %>

